The paper deals with modelling information diffusion on social networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the study of social networks and their properties. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes two models for information diffusion, which can be seen as software engineering solutions. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another likely category as the paper uses data from a social network to validate the proposed models. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with the structure of information cascade trees. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the stochastic process of information diffusion, which can have implications for cybersecurity and privacy.
